,''originalwidth'':''2400'',''originalheight'':''1189''}" style="padding-bottom: 49.541666666667%"></div></div><button class="mainNav__level2--close"><span class="mainNav__level2--close-icon"></span><span class="sr-only">Close Menü</span></button></div></div></li></ul></nav></div></div></div><div class="header__wrapper--logo"><div class="header--logo"><a href="/en" title="Homepage"><img alt="Homepage" src="https://www.swisscontact.online/_Resources/Static/Packages/Internezzo.Neos/Images/logo_swisscontact.svg?bust=435ac641" /></a></div></div></div></header><div class="page"><div class="body--overlay d-print-none" data-internezzo-body--overlay></div><div class="header__image content--header__image"><div class="header__image--inner"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''d3c0d7fd-293d-4dcb-b10c-1a8aeb72248b'',''name'':''Bangladesh_Astha_awarenenss_raising.jpg'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''fa202672658ff713b54a4fa2878479b9e84c5d34'',''maxwidth'':''6000'',''originalwidth'':''6000'',''originalheight'':''2975''}" style="padding-bottom: 49.583333333333%"></div></div></div><div class="nav__breadcrumb"><ol><li class="nav__breadcrumb--item"><a class="breadcrumb--link" href="/en"><span class="nav__breadcrumb--text">Home</span></a><span class="nav__breadcrumb--divider"></span></li><li class="nav__breadcrumb--item lastItem"><span class="nav__breadcrumb--text">Media</span><span class="nav__breadcrumb--divider"></span></li></ol></div><div class="lead__content container"><div class="row justify-content-md-center"><div class="col-12 col-md-10 col-lg-8"><div class="main__content--headline"><h1>Media</h1></div><div class="ce__lead"><div class="ce__lead--content"><div class="ce__lead--text">Media professionals find the latest media releases and contact persons for media enquiries here.&nbsp;</div></div></div></div></div></div><main class="main__content"><div class="neos-contentcollection"><div class="container content__text"><div class="row justify-content-md-center"><div class="col-12 col-md-10 col-lg-8"><h3>Media Contact</h3></div></div></div><div class="container teaserGroup teaserGroup__3col" data-internezz-teaser--teasergroup><div class="row" data-internezzo-teaser--teasergroup-teasercontainer><div class="teaser__element teaser__3col col-12 col-md-6 col-xl-4 " data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="f1dcf491-a237-483c-aaa3-b2021d9375d5"><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__image"><a href="/en/team-members/head-office/theres-meyer"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''68a8c9f0-3292-400f-8ae2-b855b47c6263'',''name'':''Theres-Meyer_bw_web.jpg'',''title'':''Theres Meyer'',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''7c89796242403ad885480eaf323cc377bd6f9e66'',''maxwidth'':''928'',''originalwidth'':''928'',''originalheight'':''619''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.702586206897%"></div></a></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-workingArea"><span>Markets & Partnerships</span></div></div></div><div class="teaser__box--title">Theres Meyer</div><div class="teaser__box--text">Content & PR Manager</div></div><a href="/en/team-members/head-office/theres-meyer" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div></div></div><div class="container content__text"><div class="row justify-content-md-center"><div class="col-12 col-md-10 col-lg-8"></div></div></div><div class="container teaserGroup teaserGroup__3col" data-internezz-teaser--teasergroup><div class="row" data-internezzo-teaser--teasergroup-teasercontainer><div class="teaserGroup__headline col-12"><h2>Latest Media Releases</h2></div><div class="teaser__element teaser__3col col-12 col-md-6 col-xl-4 " data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="00a6f346-7361-4f6f-9510-bf69766ff644"><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__image"><a href="/en/news/annual-report-2025-international-cooperation-development-through-expertise-and-partnership"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''6aa1b737-8363-4f1c-b943-dfcd9cab661d'',''name'':''DSC00021.jpg'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''83bfe882f5cdf238f86118451d61b3a86b78ed07'',''maxwidth'':''6923'',''originalwidth'':''6923'',''originalheight'':''4613''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.632962588473%"></div></a></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-country"><span>Switzerland</span></div></div></div><div class="teaser__box--date">13.05.2026</div><div class="teaser__box--title">Annual Report 2025: International cooperation:<br>development through expertise and partnership</div><div class="teaser__box--text">In 2025, international development cooperation progressed against a backdrop of rising geopolitical uncertainty. Swisscontact responded by focusing on relevant, future-oriented projects that created value for partner countries and Switzerland alike.&nbsp;Programmes in skills development helped people acquire practical skills, resulting in new jobs and income-generating activities. The strengthening of local vocational education systems was a priority as well. At the same time, entrepreneurs and small businesses gained better access to markets, services, and finance.</div></div><a href="/en/news/annual-report-2025-international-cooperation-development-through-expertise-and-partnership" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div><div class="teaser__element teaser__3col col-12 col-md-6 col-xl-4 " data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="f8a30b15-e0dd-4944-9699-4085299cb912"><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__image"><a href="/en/news/swisscontact-annual-report-2024-international-cooperation-promoting-prosperity-and-stability"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''b6d5b397-7625-4110-a7b8-54035878aaa2'',''name'':''AR24_Fav_02_web.jpg'',''title'':''Swisscontact Annual Report 24 - Villageworks, Cambodia'',''alt'':''Swisscontact Annual Report 24 - Villageworks, Cambodia'',''hash'':''d871d6d11fe55fcc50750dc3ec6b98bf3ea483a5'',''maxwidth'':''3600'',''originalwidth'':''3600'',''originalheight'':''2399''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.638888888889%"></div></a></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-country"><span>Switzerland</span></div></div></div><div class="teaser__box--date">15.05.2025</div><div class="teaser__box--title">Annual Report 2024: International cooperation: promoting prosperity and stability &nbsp;</div><div class="teaser__box--text">The challenges for international development cooperation were more significant than ever in 2024. Despite armed conflicts in various regions of the world and natural disasters, Swisscontact was able to continue or launch 133 projects in 41 countries worldwide. This was made possible thanks to the many strong partnerships that Swisscontact has built over the past years.&nbsp;</div></div><a href="/en/news/swisscontact-annual-report-2024-international-cooperation-promoting-prosperity-and-stability" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div><div class="teaser__element teaser__3col col-12 col-md-6 col-xl-4 " data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="a3ddc866-c867-4c31-86cb-731c04b216c8"><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__image"><a href="/en/news/2023-Annual-Report-far-sighted-development-cooperation-more-important-than-ever2023"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''0834d5cc-1619-463a-b636-7c1f21ab0d61'',''name'':''Swisscontact_Content_Gathering_for_TVETs___-_RV8_2673.jpg'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''8ca634ebc2d88c5f1cfe622651f0c7f898d44dda'',''maxwidth'':''5000'',''originalwidth'':''5000'',''originalheight'':''3331''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.62%"></div></a></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-country"><span>Switzerland</span></div></div></div><div class="teaser__box--date">24.05.2024</div><div class="teaser__box--title">2023 Annual Report: Far-sighted development cooperation more important than ever</div><div class="teaser__box--text">International development cooperation in 2023 was marked by major upheavals. Swisscontact is convinced that has never been more vital for development cooperation to exercise foresight and adapt promptly to changing circumstances. In 2023, a total of 139 projects were successfully carried out in 41 countries. Swisscontact’s Foundation Council is now even stronger after gaining three new members from the private sector.</div></div><a href="/en/news/2023-Annual-Report-far-sighted-development-cooperation-more-important-than-ever2023" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div><div class="teaser__element teaser__3col col-12 col-md-6 col-xl-4 " data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="a507714c-451f-4b20-9c51-34ae33bcd88c"><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__image"><a href="/en/news/2022-a-challenging-year-and-a-reinvigorated-foundation-council"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''a195142f-3581-49a3-ab08-1a4f7436ec12'',''name'':''_DSC0371.jpg'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''4dcb41ad8fb22121a6d97840b8723d2153c88c32'',''maxwidth'':''5472'',''originalwidth'':''5472'',''originalheight'':''3646''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.630116959064%"></div></a></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-country"><span>Switzerland</span></div></div></div><div class="teaser__box--date">17.05.2023</div><div class="teaser__box--title">2022: a challenging year and a reinvigorated Foundation Council</div><div class="teaser__box--text">Although the negative circumstances this past year have presented difficulties for international development cooperation around the world, in 2022 Swisscontact was still able to successfully implement 131 projects in 41 countries. These included business development projects, thanks to which around 3.8 million people gained access to better products and services. Starting in 2023, Swisscontact will gain even more knowledge and experience through our Foundation Council.</div></div><a href="/en/news/2022-a-challenging-year-and-a-reinvigorated-foundation-council" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div><div class="teaser__element teaser__3col col-12 col-md-6 col-xl-4 " data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="6401b1e0-76cd-48f5-bc07-badea9826e65"><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__image"><a href="/en/news/international-development-cooperation-2021-viable-partnerships-are-key"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''bacc1590-a3da-4531-a458-9e314ceb4899'',''name'':''Cover_Annual_Report_2021_web.jpg'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''333023d5d6d9224762f111f896b608059f56e533'',''maxwidth'':''2400'',''originalwidth'':''2400'',''originalheight'':''1599''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.625%"></div></a></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-country"><span>Switzerland</span></div></div></div><div class="teaser__box--date">20.05.2022</div><div class="teaser__box--title">International development cooperation 2021:<br>Viable partnerships are key</div><div class="teaser__box--text">In 2021, Swisscontact implemented 122 projects in 40 countries. Despite insecurity and ongoing restrictions due to the Covid-19 pandemic, 101,800 people around the world nevertheless completed programmes in vocational education, business training, and labour market integration. In addition, 56,300 new jobs were created or spared from downsizing.</div></div><a href="/en/news/international-development-cooperation-2021-viable-partnerships-are-key" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div><div class="teaser__element teaser__3col col-12 col-md-6 col-xl-4 " data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="b8d54758-10c9-4ab0-9a1b-5d15388f3f16"><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__image"><a href="/en/news/new-member-of-the-swisscontact-executive-board?country=ch"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''1de24aa0-73d7-46d2-8073-0e12c35b54db'',''name'':''Franz_Kehl.jpg'',''title'':''Franz Kehl'',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''dba286e1b558416001e71cbe6ee8db012e543abc'',''maxwidth'':''1918'',''originalwidth'':''1918'',''originalheight'':''1279''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.684045881126%"></div></a></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-country"><span>Switzerland</span></div></div></div><div class="teaser__box--date">14.09.2021</div><div class="teaser__box--title">New member of the Swisscontact Executive Board: Franz Kehl is the new Director of Products &amp; Solutions</div><div class="teaser__box--text">After an extensive and rigorous evaluation procedure, the Swisscontact Foundation Council has appointed Franz Kehl to the Executive Board as its newest member and Director of Products &amp; Solutions. He will begin his tenure at Swisscontact in January 2022.</div></div><a href="/en/news/new-member-of-the-swisscontact-executive-board?country=ch" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div><div class="teaser__element teaser__3col col-12 col-md-6 col-xl-4 " data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="07e1e8c1-5008-4de7-aaae-4cf98f0e8650"><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__image"><a href="/en/news/a-new-management-duo-has-taken-the-helm"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''95c57f69-2fee-48a0-967c-62b3a2eb41ef'',''name'':''Handover-Event_07.jpg'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''f6d4b15d7095f877800269bdc760f5ef8d2715aa'',''maxwidth'':''2000'',''originalwidth'':''2000'',''originalheight'':''1332''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.6%"></div></a></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-country"><span>Switzerland</span></div></div></div><div class="teaser__box--date">03.06.2021</div><div class="teaser__box--title">A new management duo has taken the helm</span><span>&nbsp;</div><div class="teaser__box--text">The former Chairman of the Swisscontact Foundation Board, Heinrich M. Lanz, passed the torch to his successor Thomas D. Meyer on 2 June 2021. Meyer and the new CEO, Philippe Schneuwly, who takes over from Samuel Bon, will form the new team at the head of Swisscontact from June 2021.</span><span>&nbsp;</div></div><a href="/en/news/a-new-management-duo-has-taken-the-helm" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div><div class="teaser__element teaser__3col col-12 col-md-6 col-xl-4 " data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="7de474c3-fea0-48c3-a98a-d1d2e6be003c"><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__image"><a href="/en/news/international-development-cooperation-in-the-covid-year-2020-using-digitalisation-to-foster-resilience-in-people-and-businesses"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''6b3edb96-83c7-433c-a4f5-65861b039487'',''name'':''Annual_Report_2020_06.jpg'',''title'':''Basic practice turning by a student of the community college manufacture Bantaeng, South Sulawesi, Indonesia'',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''81b968c80d2683537c4e38be5a05b9ad9e9f0c4a'',''maxwidth'':''5184'',''originalwidth'':''5184'',''originalheight'':''3454''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.628086419753%"></div></a></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--date">12.05.2021</div><div class="teaser__box--title">International development cooperation in the “COVID year 2020”: using digitalisation to foster resilience in people and businesses</span><span>&nbsp;</div><div class="teaser__box--text">In 2020, Swisscontact worked in a total of 39 countries and implemented 117 projects. Thanks to the long-term approach and strong local roots of these projects, 94,900 people were able to complete programmes in skills development, entrepreneurship and labour-market insertion despite the COVID-19 pandemic. In the area of company development, 870,200 farmers and SMEs received access to better services and products, enabling them to more effectively weather the current crisis.</span><span>&nbsp;</div></div><a href="/en/news/international-development-cooperation-in-the-covid-year-2020-using-digitalisation-to-foster-resilience-in-people-and-businesses" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div><div class="teaser__element teaser__3col col-12 col-md-6 col-xl-4 " data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="da4aef6b-1425-438b-b2e6-07f3f575b6c0"><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__image"><a href="/en/news/new-ceo-of-swisscontact"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''edfd9914-5754-465a-9b4c-e2221cc271a5'',''name'':''Philippe_Schneuwly_04.jpg'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''1f513862ce94ee3760cb43123678a3cac4b8ed86'',''maxwidth'':''2000'',''originalwidth'':''2000'',''originalheight'':''1332''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.6%"></div></a></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-country"><span>Switzerland</span></div></div></div><div class="teaser__box--date">04.03.2021</div><div class="teaser__box--title">New CEO of Swisscontact</div><div class="teaser__box--text">We are pleased to inform you that we have now reached a decision as to who will succeed Samuel Bon as CEO of Swisscontact.</div></div><a href="/en/news/new-ceo-of-swisscontact" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div></div></div><div class="container neos-nodetypes-form">
