Nav__text">Corporate Partnerships</span></a></li><li class="mainNav__item level2"><a href="/en/get-involved-with-us/philanthropic-engagement"><span class="mainNav__text">Philanthropic Engagement</span></a></li><li class="mainNav__item level2"><a href="/en/get-involved-with-us/public-development-cooperation"><span class="mainNav__text">Public Development Cooperation</span></a></li><li class="mainNav__item level2"><a href="/en/get-involved-with-us/support-swisscontact"><span class="mainNav__text">Support Swisscontact</span></a></li></ul></div><div class="mainNav__level2--image"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''6159ff88-c18f-482f-8d27-9193ae08a971'',''name'':''IND_SS4C_DSCF8110.jpeg'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''531094119d262dbc60017c71d819ca76d8665e75'',''maxwidth'':''2400'',''originalwidth'':''2400'',''originalheight'':''1189''}" style="padding-bottom: 49.541666666667%"></div></div><button class="mainNav__level2--close"><span class="mainNav__level2--close-icon"></span><span class="sr-only">Close Menü</span></button></div></div></li><li class="mainNav__item level1"><a href="/en/news"><span class="mainNav__text">News</span></a></li><li data-nezzo-mainnav-haschilds class="mainNav__item level1 sub"><a href="/en/about-us"><span class="mainNav__text">About us</span></a><div class="mainNav__level2--wrapper"><div class="mainNav__level2--content"><div><div class="mainNav__item--parent level2"><a href="/en/about-us"><span class="mainNav__text">About us</span></a></div><ul class="mainNav__level2" data-nezzo-mainnav-level="2"><li class="mainNav__item level2"><a href="/en/about-us/mission-and-guiding-principles"><span class="mainNav__text">Mission and guiding principles</span></a></li><li class="mainNav__item level2"><a href="/en/about-us/sustainability-strategy"><span class="mainNav__text">Sustainability strategy</span></a></li><li class="mainNav__item level2"><a href="/en/about-us/code-of-conduct"><span class="mainNav__text">Code of conduct</span></a></li><li class="mainNav__item level2"><a href="/en/about-us/foundation"><span class="mainNav__text">Foundation</span></a></li><li class="mainNav__item level2"><a href="/en/about-us/team"><span class="mainNav__text">Team</span></a></li><li class="mainNav__item level2"><a href="/en/about-us/history"><span class="mainNav__text">History</span></a></li><li class="mainNav__item level2"><a href="/en/about-us/annual-reports"><span class="mainNav__text">Annual reports</span></a></li><li class="mainNav__item level2"><a href="/en/about-us/jobs"><span class="mainNav__text">Jobs</span></a></li></ul></div><div class="mainNav__level2--image"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''a486b7d2-045a-4a77-baa1-704e4851e68c'',''name'':''KHM_SDP_Back_Cover_1.jpeg'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''3fbb2100ff065e1f1d307db2c88a6e39ceba85cc'',''maxwidth'':''2400'',''originalwidth'':''2400'',''originalheight'':''1189''}" style="padding-bottom: 49.541666666667%"></div></div><button class="mainNav__level2--close"><span class="mainNav__level2--close-icon"></span><span class="sr-only">Close Menü</span></button></div></div></li></ul></nav></div></div></div><div class="header__wrapper--logo"><div class="header--logo"><a href="/en" title="Homepage"><img alt="Homepage" src="https://www.swisscontact.online/_Resources/Static/Packages/Internezzo.Neos/Images/logo_swisscontact.svg?bust=435ac641" /></a></div></div></div></header><div class="page"><div class="body--overlay d-print-none" data-internezzo-body--overlay></div><div class="header__image content--header__image"><div class="header__image--inner"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''085076a2-c821-4e75-9e89-d4b770ac3cad'',''name'':''3819.jpg'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''442fa3c71084e752b3cea500b74d004335044139'',''maxwidth'':''5760'',''originalwidth'':''5760'',''originalheight'':''2853''}" style="padding-bottom: 49.53125%"></div></div></div><div class="nav__breadcrumb"><ol><li class="nav__breadcrumb--item"><a class="breadcrumb--link" href="/en"><span class="nav__breadcrumb--text">Home</span></a><span class="nav__breadcrumb--divider"></span></li><li class="nav__breadcrumb--item"><a class="breadcrumb--link" href="/en/where-we-work"><span class="nav__breadcrumb--text">Where we work</span></a><span class="nav__breadcrumb--divider"></span></li><li class="nav__breadcrumb--item lastItem"><span class="nav__breadcrumb--text">Bolivia</span><span class="nav__breadcrumb--divider"></span></li></ol></div><div class="lead__content sideContent container"><div class="row"><div class="sideContent--left col-12 col-lg-6 col-xl-7"><div class="main__content--headline"><h1>Bolivia</h1></div><div class="ce__lead"><div class="ce__lead--content"><div class="ce__lead--text">Bolivia faces the challenge of improving its sustainable production and motivating a greater social integration of individuals and families in the economy and in the service, marketing and technology markets. To contribute to the sustainable and inclusive growth of the country, we focus our work on improving the competitiveness of rural areas by applying a market systems development approach. The access to quality technical training for young people and adults in vulnerable situations, is a necessary condition for them to enter the labor market. As a third approach, Swisscontact also strengthens local capacities and knowledge in relation to the Circular Economy and Urban Mobility within the framework of Green Cities.</div></div></div></div><div class="country__sideContent col-12 col-lg-5 offset-lg-1 col-xl-4"><div class="sideContent--box"><div class="sideContent--map"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-respectheight="true" data-ari-params="{''id'':''d32d8402-5476-48a5-b5c0-bd785097a9ed'',''name'':''bolivia.png'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''682250d772e822619e06fe83cab26531d516ec10'',''maxwidth'':''668'',''originalwidth'':''668'',''originalheight'':''507''}"></div></div><div class="sideContent--headline">bolivia</div><div class="sideContent--infos"><h3><strong>facts and figures</strong></h3><ul><li>Area: 1,099,000 km²</li><li>Population: 11.5 millon</li><li>Capital: Sucre</li></ul><h3><strong>Swisscontact in Bolivia</strong></h3><ul><li>since 1988</li></ul></div></div></div></div></div><main class="main__content"><div class="backgroundContainer"><div class="container"><div class="teaserGroup teaserGroup__2col" data-internezz-teaser--teasergroup><div class="row"><div class="teaserGroup__headline col-12"><h3>Projects</h3></div><div class="teaserGroup__link col-12"><a href="/en/projects?country=bo" title="View all projects from Bolivia">View all projects from Bolivia</a></div><div class="teaser__element teaser__2col col-12 col-lg-6 " data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="f6a6bcb5-58aa-4ab8-a40e-679b59b837c4"><div class="teaser__image teaser__image--2col"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''535affe0-f04b-49eb-b0f5-53f4ae9609cd'',''name'':''Picture2.png'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''2523d39d679671600d7f33a088956de53387d43f'',''maxwidth'':''585'',''originalwidth'':''585'',''originalheight'':''390''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"></div></div><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-duration"><span>2025 - 2027</span></div></div><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-country"><span>Bolivia</span></div></div><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-workingArea"><span>Green cities</span></div></div></div><div class="teaser__box--title">ProTransicion – Strengthening the Energy Transition in Bolivia</div><div class="teaser__box--text">The ProTransicion programme aims to establish favourable technical, organisational, and financial conditions to accelerate the energy transition. The programme focuses its actions on priority sectors such as industry, public buildings, and urban transport, contributing to the fulfilment of international commitments on climate mitigation and adaptation.</div></div><a href="/en/projects/protransition" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div><div class="teaser__element teaser__2col col-12 col-lg-6 " data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="56269cec-9a9e-49cb-b24b-b06ec95701ed"><div class="teaser__image teaser__image--2col"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''e186e590-5372-4f32-8780-c634ec327b0c'',''name'':''Paisajes_Amaz%C3%B3nicos_Sostenibles.jpg'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''0b76093c3748801e0c4c927c4f21bd908f822ade'',''maxwidth'':''3405'',''originalwidth'':''3405'',''originalheight'':''2268''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.607929515419%"></div></div><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-duration"><span>2025 - 2028</span></div></div><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-country"><span>Peru, Bolivia</span></div></div><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-workingArea"><span>Sustainable agriculture, Sustainable tourism</span></div></div></div><div class="teaser__box--title">Amazon Prosperity&nbsp;</div><div class="teaser__box--text">Amazon Prosperity protects forests and biodiversity, improves livelihoods for small producers and Indigenous communities in Peru and Bolivia, and cuts carbon emissions through agroforestry, inclusive value chains, and landscape management.</div></div><a href="/en/projects/amazon-prosperity" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div></div></div><div class="teaserGroup teaserGroup__3col" data-internezz-teaser--teasergroup><div class="row" data-internezzo-teaser--teasergroup-teasercontainer><div class="teaser__element teaser__3col col-12 col-md-6 col-xl-4 " data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="b9b3c6fd-29ba-42fb-817d-d1ef191e9cc4"><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__image"><a href="/en/projects/inclusive-markets-in-bolivia" title="Learn more"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''8a67488a-c0e9-47b7-8587-a748ba7a6e51'',''name'':''Mercados_Inclusivos_2020_-_2.jpeg'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''be04c92b12039f80c56a30499638d02b32b3058b'',''maxwidth'':''4894'',''originalwidth'':''4894'',''originalheight'':''3264''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.69391091132%"></div></a></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-duration"><span>2017 - 2026</span></div></div><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-country"><span>Bolivia</span></div></div><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-workingArea"><span>Sustainable agriculture</span></div></div></div><div class="teaser__box--title">Inclusive Markets in Bolivia</div><div class="teaser__box--text">The main objective of the program is "to improve the living conditions of the target population by helping them reduce their poverty situation". The purpose is "to increase the opportunities, capacities and income of the target population".The Inclusive Markets project is implemented in Bolivia with funding from the Swiss Agency for Development and...</div></div><a href="/en/projects/inclusive-markets-in-bolivia" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div><div class="teaser__element teaser__3col col-12 col-md-6 col-xl-4 " data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="40671cbd-ba40-4883-bdcc-bc3b41aa6987"><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__image"><a href="/en/projects/technical-innovation-for-sustainable-development-and-an-equitable-green-economic-transition-green-skills-training" title="Learn more"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''fd738517-5c65-4b41-8a85-265d331c7142'',''name'':''23Electricidad_Industrial.jpg'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''f5fd244b30db8bd41687070cca5c7cb3f58c1d98'',''maxwidth'':''3000'',''originalwidth'':''3000'',''originalheight'':''1999''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.633333333333%"></div></a></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-duration"><span>2024 - 2026</span></div></div><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-country"><span>Bolivia</span></div></div><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-workingArea"><span>Initial vocational education and training</span></div></div></div><div class="teaser__box--title">Technical innovation for sustainable development and an equitable green economic transition (Green Skills Training)</div><div class="teaser__box--text">The INNOTEC project seeks to strengthen green competences in public technical training, improving the employability of male and female students by connecting them with sustainable enterprises supported by Swisscontact in Bolivia.</div></div><a href="/en/projects/technical-innovation-for-sustainable-development-and-an-equitable-green-economic-transition-green-skills-training" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div><div class="teaser__element teaser__3col col-12 col-md-6 col-xl-4 " data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="533c1150-4ea1-4c0b-bc30-be3c155b7aa4"><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__image"><a href="/en/projects/sec" title="Learn more"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''56c40ea9-ac6b-42db-8a3a-3e9754d00020'',''name'':''SEC_Bussink_Medicine_Nepal_2010.jpg'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''1e3aca9d8a1e42bb4bcab051e2b99e7fdc9d0df5'',''maxwidth'':''1943'',''originalwidth'':''1943'',''originalheight'':''1296''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.700977869274%"></div></a></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-country"><span>Benin, Bolivia, Cambodia, Kosovo, Nepal, Peru</span></div></div><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-workingArea"><span>Growth entrepreneurship</span></div></div></div><div class="teaser__box--title">Senior Expert Contact</div><div class="teaser__box--text"> Promoting entrepreneurship through expertise - Imparting technical skills through volunteer work Through their services, Senior Expert Contact (SEC) experts provide hands-on, direct support to companies and institutions in their efforts to grow. <br />
Website</div></div><a href="/en/projects/sec" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="container"><div class="teaserGroup teaserGroup__3col" data-internezz-teaser--teasergroup><div class="row" data-internezzo-teaser--teasergroup-teasercontainer><div class="teaserGroup__headline col-12"><h3>News</h3></div><div class="teaserGroup__link col-12"><a href="/en/news?country=bo" title="View all news from Bolivia">View all news from Bolivia</a></div><div class="teaser__element teaser__3col col-12 col-md-6 col-xl-4 teaser--news" data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="ef7bb422-66c6-4463-bf08-44e917e1dcc2"><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__image"><a href="/en/news/plastics-treaty-negotiations-end-without-agreement-a-setback-for-human-and-planetary-health" title="Learn more"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''49733d0a-e13b-43b0-87da-babe69d7535c'',''name'':''SCP_Laos.jpeg'',''title'':''Swisscontact Project for Plastic Free Tourism in Laos'',''alt'':''A waste picker sorting recyclable plastic at the landfill site'',''hash'':''dc55300738aa707b120fbbc1626cfa3788b1a3c1'',''maxwidth'':''4032'',''originalwidth'':''4032'',''originalheight'':''2688''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"></div></a></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-country"><span>Switzerland, Laos, Bolivia</span></div></div><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-workingArea"><span>Green cities, Green Employment</span></div></div></div><div class="teaser__box--date">25.08.2025</div><div class="teaser__box--title">Plastics Treaty Negotiations End Without Agreement: a setback for human and planetary health</div><div class="teaser__box--text">After nearly three years of intense negotiations, the world’s effort to establish a legally binding Global Plastics Treaty has come to a disappointing halt. The fifth and final session of the Intergovernmental Negotiating Committee (INC-5.2), held from August 5–14 in Geneva, brought together delegates from 184 countries to address the escalating plastic pollution crisis. Despite the urgency and global consensus on the need for action, the talks ended without agreement.</div></div><a href="/en/news/plastics-treaty-negotiations-end-without-agreement-a-setback-for-human-and-planetary-health" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div><div class="teaser__element teaser__3col col-12 col-md-6 col-xl-4 teaser--news" data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="d181792c-a60c-4642-9035-6bc2cd0d03cb"><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__image"><a href="/en/news/composting-as-a-key-solution-for-waste-management-and-sustainable-agriculture" title="Learn more"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''ef510d4d-6c52-44eb-8b80-a24ea7ea3e43'',''name'':''Negocios_Verdes%2C_una_alternativa_al_problema_de_los_residuos.00_01_23_01.Still002.png'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''332bd6971fd40041e8c8240af247efdba901b598'',''maxwidth'':''1081'',''originalwidth'':''1081'',''originalheight'':''720''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.604995374653%"></div></a></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-country"><span>Bolivia, Colombia</span></div></div><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-workingArea"><span>Sustainable agriculture, Green cities</span></div></div></div><div class="teaser__box--date">18.11.2024</div><div class="teaser__box--title">Composting as a key solution for waste management and sustainable agriculture</div><div class="teaser__box--text">Swisscontact is leading an initiative to promote composting in Latin America as a key solution to address waste management challenges and encourage sustainable agricultural practices.&nbsp;</div></div><a href="/en/news/composting-as-a-key-solution-for-waste-management-and-sustainable-agriculture" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div><div class="teaser__element teaser__3col col-12 col-md-6 col-xl-4 teaser--news" data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="73992d32-b4b1-406c-a94e-44823b0a0170"><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__image"><a href="/en/news/recycling-turning-waste-into-wealth" title="Learn more"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''8a12a3cf-2a7e-4c65-8366-73c0c2b75671'',''name'':''Negocios_Verdes%2C_una_alternativa_al_problema_de_los_residuos.00_01_04_28.Still005.png'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''90ade1d883714325ede5215e78df006c5179f890'',''maxwidth'':''1081'',''originalwidth'':''1081'',''originalheight'':''720''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.604995374653%"></div></a></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-country"><span>Bolivia, Colombia</span></div></div><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-workingArea"><span>Green cities</span></div></div></div><div class="teaser__box--date">18.11.2024</div><div class="teaser__box--title">Recycling: Turning waste into wealth</div><div class="teaser__box--text">The circular economy offers a route to sustainable development and prosperity in Latin America by providing practical solutions to address the region''s environmental and economic challenges. By adopting this approach, Latin American countries can harness their resources more efficiently, strengthen their local economies and promote a more equitable and resilient future for all.</div></div><a href="/en/news/recycling-turning-waste-into-wealth" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="container"><div class="multicolumn__twoCol"><div class="row twoCol--4and8"><div class="twoCol--left col-12 col-lg-4"><div class="content__director"><div class="director--image"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''6484d015-765b-49a7-9134-04482ca0d753'',''name'':''SARA_METHAIS_-_DIRECTORA_PA%C3%8DS_BOLIVIA.png'',''title'':''Sara Methais, directora de país swisscontact Bolivia'',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''53ebc727976dc7a2f3fde515f95ad3ac38f762b7'',''maxwidth'':''1621'',''originalwidth'':''1621'',''originalheight'':''1080''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.625539790253%"></div></div><div class="director--text"><div class="director--role"><span>Directora País</span><span>&nbsp;</span></div><div class="director--name">Sarah Metais</div></div></div></div><div class="2col--right col-12 col-lg-8"><div class="content__facts"><div class="facts--headline"><h3>Swisscontact in Bolivia</h3></div><div class="facts--text"><p>Swisscontact started working in Bolivia in 1988. Since then, it has implemented various programs and projects that promote inclusive development – economic, social and environmental – offering economically and socially disadvantaged people the opportunity to improve their lives using their own initiative.&nbsp;</p><p>Our work focuses on rural development projects, professional technical training, environment and climate change mitigation, which are concentrated in four main areas: Vocational Education and Skills Development, Insertion in the Labour Market, Sustainable Agriculture, Commerce and Green Cities.&nbsp;</p><p>Through our systemic approach and our role as facilitators, we work with a wide network of local stakeholders both in the public and private sector as well as with the academic sector.&nbsp;</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="neos-contentcollection"><div class="container content__button"><div class="d-print-none btn"><p class="btn--linked"><a href="https://www.swisscontact.online/es/paises/bolivia">Additional news and content on the&nbsp;spanish version of this page</span><span>&nbsp;</a></p></div></div><div class="teaser__element teaser__fullsize" data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="c86eed29-5ceb-45b5-9dd6-ee78f5e67cd7"><div class="teaser__image"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''dae2095a-8bef-4c8a-82ad-39d1b800c804'',''name'':''HO6A4109.jpg'',''title'':''Aire Limpio_La Paz_Bolivia'',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''c1936d761a58734e5dbf36cc1c5eb8bed51c2e2c'',''maxwidth'':''5760'',''originalwidth'':''5760'',''originalheight'':''2879''}" style="padding-bottom: 49.982638888889%"></div></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="container"><div class="teaser__box--wrapper col-lg-8 offset-lg-2 col-xl-5 offset-xl-0 col-xxl-4"><div class="teaser__box--content"><div class="teaser__box--tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-duration"><span>2010 - 2017</span></div></div><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-country"><span>Bolivia</span></div></div><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-workingArea"><span>Green cities</span></div></div></div><div class="teaser__box--title">The Journey and Key Achievements of Aire Limpio</div><div class="teaser__box--text">The Aire Limpio (Clean Air) Project contributed to the protection of Bolivia’s population, as well as the environment against the effects of air pollution. The results: CO2 emissions have decreased by 370,000 tonnes, and 12 Bolivian cities have designed sustainable mobility plans and are currently implementing them. Aside from this, a national air quality measurement network has been installed. The Aire Limpio project was an SDC project and implemented by Swisscontact from 2003 until 2017.</div></div><div class="teaser__box--link"><a href="/en/projects/aire-limpio" class="teaser--link" title="Encuentra Más (en inglés)"><span class="teaser--link-text">Encuentra Más (en inglés)</span></a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="container teaserGroup teaserGroup__2col" data-internezz-teaser--teasergroup><div class="row"></div></div></div><div class="container" data-nezzo-usercentr