ref="/en/about-us/code-of-conduct"><span class="mainNav__text">Code of conduct</span></a></li><li class="mainNav__item level2"><a href="/en/about-us/foundation"><span class="mainNav__text">Foundation</span></a></li><li class="mainNav__item level2"><a href="/en/about-us/team"><span class="mainNav__text">Team</span></a></li><li class="mainNav__item level2"><a href="/en/about-us/history"><span class="mainNav__text">History</span></a></li><li class="mainNav__item level2"><a href="/en/about-us/annual-reports"><span class="mainNav__text">Annual reports</span></a></li><li class="mainNav__item level2"><a href="/en/about-us/jobs"><span class="mainNav__text">Jobs</span></a></li></ul></div><div class="mainNav__level2--image"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''a486b7d2-045a-4a77-baa1-704e4851e68c'',''name'':''KHM_SDP_Back_Cover_1.jpeg'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''3fbb2100ff065e1f1d307db2c88a6e39ceba85cc'',''maxwidth'':''2400'',''originalwidth'':''2400'',''originalheight'':''1189''}" style="padding-bottom: 49.541666666667%"></div></div><button class="mainNav__level2--close"><span class="mainNav__level2--close-icon"></span><span class="sr-only">Close Menü</span></button></div></div></li></ul></nav></div></div></div><div class="header__wrapper--logo"><div class="header--logo"><a href="/en" title="Homepage"><img alt="Homepage" src="https://www.swisscontact.online/_Resources/Static/Packages/Internezzo.Neos/Images/logo_swisscontact.svg?bust=435ac641" /></a></div></div></div></header><div class="page"><div class="body--overlay d-print-none" data-internezzo-body--overlay></div><div class="header__image content--header__image"><div class="header__image--inner"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''6c697e89-f57c-4aac-800b-32659121872d'',''name'':''Header_Image_-_Burundi.jpg'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''08569eab11adc60f40bc98d9e49d40c311e593d1'',''maxwidth'':''4000'',''originalwidth'':''4000'',''originalheight'':''1982''}" style="padding-bottom: 49.55%"></div></div></div><div class="nav__breadcrumb"><ol><li class="nav__breadcrumb--item"><a class="breadcrumb--link" href="/en"><span class="nav__breadcrumb--text">Home</span></a><span class="nav__breadcrumb--divider"></span></li><li class="nav__breadcrumb--item"><a class="breadcrumb--link" href="/en/where-we-work"><span class="nav__breadcrumb--text">Where we work</span></a><span class="nav__breadcrumb--divider"></span></li><li class="nav__breadcrumb--item lastItem"><span class="nav__breadcrumb--text">Burundi</span><span class="nav__breadcrumb--divider"></span></li></ol></div><div class="lead__content sideContent container"><div class="row"><div class="sideContent--left col-12 col-lg-6 col-xl-7"><div class="main__content--headline"><h1>Burundi</h1></div><div class="ce__lead"><div class="ce__lead--content"><div class="ce__lead--text">Burundi, a landlocked country covering 27,834 km², has been marked by socio-political instability over the past three decades. Densely populated, with more than 12 million residents, of whom 50.4% are women (2019), Burundi is the second most densely populated country in Africa (after Rwanda), with population density reaching up to 470 inhabitants per km² in the most densely populated areas.<br>The country is also characterised by a very young population: 48% are under the age of 15, and 51% of the working-age population (2.5 million people) are between 15 and 35 years old, alongside a high population growth rate of 3.3% per year. With a high fertility rate of 5.5 children per woman, the population is expected to double by 2050.</div></div></div></div><div class="country__sideContent col-12 col-lg-5 offset-lg-1 col-xl-4"><div class="sideContent--box"><div class="sideContent--map"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-respectheight="true" data-ari-params="{''id'':''929da08f-e9cc-43b4-9382-a196d4f758e6'',''name'':''burundi.png'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''f3533f155af3c6031c75b97fdb6574c85af46e75'',''maxwidth'':''663'',''originalwidth'':''663'',''originalheight'':''503''}"></div></div><div class="sideContent--headline">burundi</div><div class="sideContent--infos"><h3><strong>fact and Figures</strong></h3><ul><li>Area: 27,830 km²</li><li>Population: 10.6 million</li><li>Political capital: Gitega</li><li>Economic capital: Bujumbura</li></ul><h3><strong>Swisscontact in Burundi</strong></h3><ul><li>since 2017</li></ul></div></div></div></div></div><main class="main__content"><div class="container"><div class="teaserGroup teaserGroup__3col" data-internezz-teaser--teasergroup><div class="row" data-internezzo-teaser--teasergroup-teasercontainer><div class="teaserGroup__headline col-12"><h3>News</h3></div><div class="teaserGroup__link col-12"><a href="/en/news?country=bi" title="View all news from Burundi">View all news from Burundi</a></div><div class="teaser__element teaser__3col col-12 col-md-6 col-xl-4 teaser--news" data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="1c99d156-f328-44b1-82b3-9693ce75281e"><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__image"><a href="/en/news/promost-iv-strengthening-the-impact-of-the-dual-apprenticeship-training-system" title="Learn more"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''98f623d2-5ac1-4bcb-b82a-ff297a3a8d0c'',''name'':''BU_2.jpg'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''acf4cefd3046eea316ed96104058557939f65cac'',''maxwidth'':''921'',''originalwidth'':''921'',''originalheight'':''614''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"></div></a></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-country"><span>Burundi</span></div></div><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-workingArea"><span>Initial vocational education and training</span></div></div></div><div class="teaser__box--date">11.02.2025</div><div class="teaser__box--title">PROMOST IV: Strengthening the Impact of the Dual Apprenticeship Training System</div><div class="teaser__box--text">Aristide still remembers the first day he pushed the door of the Hotel Club du Lac Tanganyika as an apprentice. His impeccably fitted apron, a mixture of excitement and apprehension in his eyes, he knew that this day marked the beginning of a new adventure. At that time, he was still unaware that ten months later, this same hotel would become his employer.<br><br>&nbsp;Like him, other young people have had the opportunity to join a dual apprenticeship training, a program that combines theory and professional immersion. This model is based on an alternation between the Vocational Training Centres (CFP) and partner companies. 80% of the time, apprentices are in the field, confronted with the reality of the profession, and 20% in theoretical training, thus refining their knowledge and skills.</div></div><a href="/en/news/promost-iv-strengthening-the-impact-of-the-dual-apprenticeship-training-system" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div><div class="teaser__element teaser__3col col-12 col-md-6 col-xl-4 teaser--news" data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="0a7a59cd-d1b5-469a-8c87-a4d88b732fbd"><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__image"><a href="/en/news/defying-odds-the-story-of-eliane-and-her-entrepreneurship-journey" title="Learn more"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''195112de-3e2d-47ee-8ebe-63e9ef279d5d'',''name'':''Eliane_la_coiffeuse_2.jpeg'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''11802a73f81db220e8061855d5009ca37bce4b60'',''maxwidth'':''810'',''originalwidth'':''810'',''originalheight'':''540''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"></div></a></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-country"><span>Burundi</span></div></div></div><div class="teaser__box--date">05.06.2024</div><div class="teaser__box--title">Defying Odds: The Story of Eliane and Her Entrepreneurship Journey</div><div class="teaser__box--text">Eliane''s Transformational Journey: From Poverty to Entrepreneurial Success</div></div><a href="/en/news/defying-odds-the-story-of-eliane-and-her-entrepreneurship-journey" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div><div class="teaser__element teaser__3col col-12 col-md-6 col-xl-4 teaser--news" data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="7a37a096-ff72-40ea-92dc-08227faaa422"><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__image"><a href="/en/news/pascal-the-unstoppable-a-young-man-s-journey-to-becoming-a-carpenter" title="Learn more"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''de558575-5968-446e-becc-6a7d4ab222bf'',''name'':''MicrosoftTeams-image_%284%29.png'',''title'':''young people in wood working workshop'',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''4017ba838b27e24b12601dfcccdcc3c6462481d1'',''maxwidth'':''4864'',''originalwidth'':''4864'',''originalheight'':''3243''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.673519736842%"></div></a></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-country"><span>Burundi</span></div></div><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-workingArea"><span>Initial vocational education and training</span></div></div></div><div class="teaser__box--date">17.10.2023</div><div class="teaser__box--title">"Pascal the unstoppable" – a young man''s journey to becoming a carpenter</div><div class="teaser__box--text">"Pascal the unstoppable" is what his friends call him. The eldest of six siblings is gradually working towards his dream of becoming a professional carpenter. Seemingly shy, Pascal Ndereyimana has seized every opportunity with determination. From idle youth to self-sufficient young man and candidate for the first edition of the Umwuga Award, Pascal shares his path to the carpentry profession.</div></div><a href="/en/news/pascal-the-unstoppable-a-young-man-s-journey-to-becoming-a-carpenter" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="container"><div class="multicolumn__twoCol"><div class="row twoCol--4and8"><div class="twoCol--left col-12 col-lg-4"><div class="content__director"><div class="director--image"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''a0c09b53-dcd9-4938-9823-a92118dcf295'',''name'':''Photo_Eva_.png'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''dd51b943daa032fa6e751bfed6d82bb1b9500d4a'',''maxwidth'':''600'',''originalwidth'':''600'',''originalheight'':''900''}" style="padding-bottom: 150%"></div></div><div class="director--text"><div class="director--role">Country Programme Manager Burundi</div><div class="director--name">Eva Pressl</div></div></div></div><div class="2col--right col-12 col-lg-8"><div class="content__facts"><div class="facts--headline"><h3>Swisscontact in Burundi</h3></div><div class="facts--text"><p><strong>Strengthening the TVET system to improve youth yccess to quality skills development</strong></p><p>Swisscontact works in Burundi to strengthen the Technical and Vocational Education and Training (TVET) system as a whole, with the aim of sustainably and inclusively improving access for young people to quality and labour market–relevant skills development. Its approach focuses on supporting key actors within the TVET ecosystem, including training institutions, public authorities, and private sector partners.</p><p>Swisscontact contributes to improving the institutional capacity of TVET providers, promoting inclusive training opportunities, and ensuring that training programmes respond to labour market needs. By fostering collaboration and partnerships among stakeholders, Swisscontact supports more coordinated and effective efforts across the system. Through this systemic approach, Swisscontact helps enable Burundian youth to acquire relevant skills that improve their employability and contribute to economic development.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="neos-contentcollection"><div class="container teaserGroup teaserGroup__3col" data-internezz-teaser--teasergroup><div class="row" data-internezzo-teaser--teasergroup-teasercontainer><div class="teaser__element teaser__3col col-12 col-md-6 col-xl-4 " data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="80487183-90b1-4169-b3ce-9594eb4a2293"><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__image"><a href="/en/projects/promotion-of-training-in-marketable-skills"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''c14bda66-4553-4e76-9aae-79efa8461136'',''name'':''NL_DSC00353_Promost_Carpenters.jpg'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''a8b1e9f3b698b532c54c32264b56aa4178483008'',''maxwidth'':''2400'',''originalwidth'':''2400'',''originalheight'':''1600''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"></div></a></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-duration"><span>2023 - 2025</span></div></div><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-country"><span>Burundi</span></div></div><div class="teaser__tagGroup"><div class="teaser__tagGroup--tag tags-workingArea"><span>Initial vocational education and training</span></div></div></div><div class="teaser__box--title">Promotion of training in marketable skills</div><div class="teaser__box--text">The overall objective of the programme is to promote skills development and job creation among young people in Burundi in the provinces of Cibitoke, Kayanza, Ngozi, Muramvya and Bujumbura Mairie, by improving their access to quality, labour market-oriented vocational training.</div></div><a href="/en/projects/promotion-of-training-in-marketable-skills" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div><div class="teaser__element teaser__3col col-12 col-md-6 col-xl-4 " data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="42953c06-578b-492a-bb3d-9028c65e7f8f"><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__image"><a href="/en/projects/promost/project-journey"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''a00a4d9f-46aa-4827-875a-aa60fd850235'',''name'':''Swisscontact_Content_Gathering_for_TVETs___-_RV8_2820.jpg'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''16fff023381ee7f98424043ab77ff05d64b2c3fd'',''maxwidth'':''5000'',''originalwidth'':''5000'',''originalheight'':''3331''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.62%"></div></a></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--title">Project Journey 2012 - 2023</div><div class="teaser__box--text"><span>The Great Lakes Region is one of the most densely populated and least urbanised areas on the African continent. In Rwanda, Burundi, and eastern Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC), subsistence agriculture remains the backbone of the economy and employs a majority of available labour. At the same time, governments are well aware that in the interest of economic growth, substantial investments in non-agricultural activities are needed to increase employment and incomes.</span><span>&nbsp;<br><br>The governments of these three countries have made skills development their stated national priority and place special emphasis on vocational training and continued education. The creation of a demand-oriented, flexible, inclusive, and high-quality vocational education system is key to rapid economic growth, fair distribution of income, and the development of a healthy society.</span><span>&nbsp;</span></div></div><a href="/en/projects/promost/project-journey" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div><div class="teaser__element teaser__3col col-12 col-md-6 col-xl-4 " data-internezzo-teaser--uniqueTeasedNodeIdentifier="5f805b19-e01d-4756-aa46-3271e47d87b1"><div class="teaser__element--wrapper"><div class="teaser__image"><a href="/en/about-us/team?country=bi"><div class="img-ari--responsive" data-ari-params="{''id'':''359441eb-7f7e-4426-b300-9efccf0c8cc5'',''name'':''equipe_teaser-image.jpg'',''title'':'''',''alt'':'''',''hash'':''3c4a20ae3c2d7d78e8c620849a8e55e2fcf8721f'',''maxwidth'':''4799'',''originalwidth'':''4799'',''originalheight'':''3197''}" style="padding-bottom: 66.61804542613%"></div></a></div><div class="teaser__box"><div class="teaser__box--title">Team</div><div class="teaser__box--text">The abilities and readiness for action of our employees are decisive for our projects’ ability to achieve sustainable impact, as well as our long-term success. As an attractive employer, Swisscontact invests in a positive management and work culture. This is defined by our fundamental understanding of development intended to serve not only our beneficiaries in project countries but our employees as well.</div></div><a href="/en/about-us/team?country=bi" class="teaser--link" title></a></div></div></div></div><div class="container content__headline"><div class="row justify-content-md-center"><div class="col-12 col-md-10 col-lg-8"><h2>Regional Reports Central, East and Southern Africa</h2></div></div></div><div class="container content__assetlist"><div class="row justify-content-md-center"><div class="col-12 col-md-10 col-lg-8"><div class="assetlist__title"></div><div class="assetlist__list"><div class="asset__element"><a target="_blank" class="asset__element--link" href="https://www.swisscontact.online/_Resources/Persistent/a/0/f/f/a0ffe5015f6aebd3e75f7ebed1854698798afb41/CESAF%20Annual%20Report%202021-2022-%20High%20Res..pdf" title="Regional Report Central, East and Southern Africa 2021"><div class="asset__element--title asset--file">Regional Report Central, East and Southern Africa 2021</div></a><div class="asset__element--infos"><span class="asset__element--size">28 MB</span></div></div><div class="asset__element"><a target="_blank" rel="noopener external" class="asset__element--link" href="https://youtu.be/F-MyUPhpQdo" title="Regional Report Video 2020/2021"><div class="asset__element--title asset--link">Regional Report Video 2020/2021</div></a></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="container" data-nezzo-usercentrics-consentplaceholder="{&quot;serviceName&quot;:&quot;amCharts&quot;,&quot;placeholderFor&quot;:&quot;Internezzo.Country:AmChartsLoader&quot;,&quot;autoReplaceOnConsent&quot;:true,&quot;replaceWith&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;data&quot;:[]}"><div class="consentplaceholder-text"><h3>We need your consent to load this content.</h3><p>We use the service of a third-party provider to offer this content. Please check the details and accept the service to activate this plug-in.</p></div><div data-nezzo-usercentrics-cmptrigger="1" class="d-print-none btn consentplaceholder-cta"><p>Cookie Settings</p></div></div><div data-nezzo-usercentrics-hide-until-consent="amCharts" class="nezzo-usercentrics-hide-until-consent country--projectmap"><div class="amcharts-world-map" data-internezzo-world-map="1" data-internezzo-world-map-locations="[{&quot;address&quot;:&quot;Ibanda, DR Congo&quot;,&quot;lat&quot;:&quot;-2.216667&quot;,&quot;lng&quot;:&quot;17.033333&quot;,&quot;project&quot;:{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Promoting Market Oriented Skills Training and Employment Creation in the Great Lakes Region&quot;,&quot;uri&quot;:&quot;\/en\/projects\/promost&quot;},&quot;countries&quot;:[&quot;bi&quot;]},{&quot;address&quot;:&quot;Kadutu, DR Congo&quot;,&quot;lat&quot;:&quot;-2.5154752&quot;,&quot;lng&quot;:&quot;28.852398&quot;,&quot;project&quot;:{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Promoting Market Oriented Skills Training and Employment Creation in the Great Lakes Region&quot;,&quot;uri&quot;:&quot;\/en\/projects\/promost&quot;},&quot;countries&quot;:[&quot;bi&quot;]},{&quot;address&quot;:&quot;Bagira, DR Congo&quot;,&quot;lat&quot;:&quot;-2.4712741&quot;,&quot;lng&quot;:&quot;28.8276355&quot;,&quot;project&quot;:{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Promoting Market Oriented Skills Training and Employment Creation in the Great Lakes Region&quot;,&quot;uri&quot;:&quot;\/en\/projects\/promost&quot;},&quot;countries&quot;:[&quot;bi&quot;]},{&quot;address&quot;:&quot;